Siloam Springs School District Athletics
September 2 at 1:08 PM ¬∑

Varsity Football will be at Pea Ridge on Friday, September 4th. Kickoff is at 7:00pm. Visiting Tickets are limited and will require a voucher to be able to purchase a $5.00 ticket at the gate. Football players have been given vouchers for their families to purchase tickets. There are still vouchers available at the HS Athletic Office for those who are wanting to go to the game. Vouchers must be picked up by an adult by noon on Friday and are limited to 4 vouchers per adult. YOU CAN NOT GET INTO THE GAME WITHOUT A VOUCHER. No students will be admitted to Friday night's game without a parent or guardian. The game will also be broadcast at siloamspringsathletics.com or on our free app SILOAM SPRINGS PANTHERS through the app store. #pantherfootball #pantherfamily

Siloam Springs Chamber of Commerce is feeling thankful with Buck Fam and 2 others.
August 13 at 11:14 AM ¬∑

It may have looked and felt different this year, but we were still able to host our Annual Back to School Breakfast for our Siloam Springs School District and John Brown University staff and faculty this year. Thank you to everyone who participated! If you have a chance, tag your favorite teacher or staff member and leave a little note of appreciation and encouragement as their jobs are going to be much more difficult this year.

We also want to send a special THANK YOU to our sponsors and those who donated door prizes, Swag Bag items, and breakfast. Thank you to Hight Jackson Associates, Alternative Design, Simmons Foods, Cobb-Vantress, Inc., Walmart Siloam Springs, Little Debbie, Harps Food Stores, Black Hills Energy, Southwestern Electric Power Company - SWEPCO, XNA Northwest Arkansas National Airport, Arkansas State Teachers Association, Gates Corporation, The Assembly, 28 Springs, Starbucks, and Sam's Club.

post_text: Letter from Superintendent Wiggins regarding Siloam Springs Virtual Academy. https://bit.ly/sssdvspm
text: Letter from Superintendent Wiggins regarding Siloam Springs Virtual Academy. https://bit.ly/sssdvspm

post_text:
Siloam Springs School District is gathering information from Siloam Springs parents and community members on the interest level of beginning a Virtual Academy. This Virtual Academy would be separate from our traditional school setting, but still a part of our district. This potential option would provide a rigorous and robust education through a virtual school platform, allowing parents and families flexible scheduling of their time and educational commitment. Students in the proposed Virtual Academy would be considered students of the Siloam Springs School District. Our intention in this survey is to gain possible student numbers to help us guide decision making and develop a viable alternative option to the traditional face-to-face environment. Please take a few minutes to let us know if this Virtual Academy option could support your family's educational experience.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSczzqB3LS-BwC8pS1LXtMz9dGVr-f-YEoBHEBpJ0KzDAJe5dA/viewform
text:
Siloam Springs School District is gathering information from Siloam Springs parents and community members on the interest level of beginning a Virtual Academy. This Virtual Academy would be separate from our traditional school setting, but still a part of our district. This potential option would provide a rigorous and robust education through a virtual school platform, allowing parents and families flexible scheduling of their time and educational commitment. Students in the proposed Virtual Academy would be considered students of the Siloam Springs School District. Our intention in this survey is to gain possible student numbers to help us guide decision making and develop a viable alternative option to the traditional face-to-face environment. Please take a few minutes to let us know if this Virtual Academy option could support your family's educational experience.

post_text:
Siloam Springs School District joins districts across the state to celebrate School Board Member Recognition Month. More than 1500 Arkansas school board members are being honored for their service and dedication to public education.

Our board members assume a crucial role in representing our students and advocating for public education. We are very proud of our members, and Arkansas School Board Recognition Month is a great time to recognize them.

post_text:
Due to tornado warnings for Siloam Springs, bus pick-up at the schools were halted this afternoon and students were sheltered in place. We have loaded students back on busses and they will be running approximately an hour later than normal. Please be patient as drivers will have to be extra cautious with the large amount of rain we received. We apologize for any inconvenience caused by our decision to shelter our students in place until the threat passed. Your children's safety is always our first priority when making these types of decisions.

Superintendent Jody Wiggins
